{meta: title Countin' The Hours Countin' The Days}
{meta: artist Bobby Bare}
{meta: composer John D. Loudermilk}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Coutin' the hours countin' the days
[C]Till I'll [D7]be back in your arms to [G]stay
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
I left Lake Charleston on 71
[C]And I drove the Highway 10
[D7]Took a ride at the second light
[G]And I turned back right again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Drove till I came to the junction 6
[C]Where it runs into 5-0-1
[A7]Stopped for gas at the Cumberland pass
[D7]And again in Burlington
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
