{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Out of Burlington
[C]I took old 70 headed west
[D7]I found me a picnic table
[G]And stretched out and I took a rest
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
I drove on across Montana Dam
[C]Till I came to Lake Wahoo
[A7]Took the prairie to the other side
[D7]I was a coming home to you
{end_of_verse}

